HEADWORD: Manumission
<hw>Man`u*mis"sion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>manumissio</ets>: cf. F. <ets>manumission</ets>. See
<er>Manumit</er>.]</ety> <def>The act of manumitting, or of liberating a
slave from bondage.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Given to slaves at their
